<subSubSection id="6483AEE13D658B5C8FCAFC40FDA53846" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2C26FD6A3D658B5C8FCAFC40FE5E3810" blockId="1.[151,1436,493,1138]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="1EED21783D658B5C8FCAFC40FEFB3FC9" bold="true" box="[198,343,995,1021]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet refers to Aladagh mountain range in SW of the capital city of Bojnord in North 
<collectingRegion id="EE5D33883D658B5C8E0DFBA9FE433810" box="[257,495,1034,1060]" country="Iran" name="Khorasan-e Shomali" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Khorassan province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2C26FD6A3D658B5C8FCAFB93FDA53846" blockId="1.[151,1436,493,1138]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="1EED21783D658B5C8FCAFB93FEFE387E" bold="true" box="[198,338,1072,1098]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Phenology:</emphasis>
—An ephemeroid species, leaf sprouting is initiated in May, flowering and fruiting is completed in mid-June (
<figureCitation id="B4A2E1EF3D658B5C8EBFFBFBFE543846" box="[435,504,1112,1138]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1943,1964]" captionTargetBox="[377,1219,1201,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-367@1.[376,1223,1201,1922]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Allium aladaghense in its natural habitat. A–B: the type location at Mt. Aladagh, A. Habit; B. A small population on stony slopes with grazed leaves. C–D: the localities at Mt. Salook, C. Plants growing in the thorn cushion Acantholimon erinaceum, a nurse bush for A. aladaghense; D. The plants in fruiting stage." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5061126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5061126/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="78E6ADE23D658B5C8F9BF834FD1F3BDB" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5061126" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5061126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5061126/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" startId="1.[151,244,1943,1964]" targetBox="[377,1219,1201,1921]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="2C26FD6A3D658B5C8F9BF834FD1F3BDB" blockId="1.[151,1436,1943,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="1EED21783D658B5C8F9BF834FEA93B98" bold="true" box="[151,261,1943,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">FIGURE 1</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="EB9986E93D658B5C8E1CF834FE633B98" authorityName="Memariani &amp; Joharchi" authorityYear="2012" box="[272,463,1943,1964]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aladaghense">
<emphasis id="1EED21783D658B5C8E1CF834FE633B98" box="[272,463,1943,1964]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Allium aladaghense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its natural habitat. A–B: the type location at Mt. Aladagh, 
<emphasis id="1EED21783D658B5C8B19F834FB813B98" bold="true" box="[1045,1069,1943,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">A.</emphasis>
Habit; 
<emphasis id="1EED21783D658B5C8B7FF834FB253B98" bold="true" box="[1139,1161,1943,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">B.</emphasis>
A small population on stony slopes with grazed leaves. C–D: the localities at Mt. Salook, 
<emphasis id="1EED21783D658B5C8DECF81BFD5B3BF9" bold="true" box="[736,759,1976,1997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">C.</emphasis>
Plants growing in the thorn cushion 
<taxonomicName id="EB9986E93D658B5C8B55F81AFAE73BFA" authorityName="Linczevski" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Jaubert &amp; Spach" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[1113,1355,1977,1998]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Acantholimon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erinaceum">
<emphasis id="1EED21783D658B5C8B55F81AFAE73BFA" box="[1113,1355,1977,1998]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Acantholimon erinaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a nurse bush for 
<taxonomicName id="EB9986E93D658B5C8FE0F879FE2C3BDB" authorityName="Memariani &amp; Joharchi" authorityYear="2012" box="[236,384,2010,2031]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aladaghense">
<emphasis id="1EED21783D658B5C8FE0F879FE2C3BDB" box="[236,384,2010,2031]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">A. aladaghense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<emphasis id="1EED21783D658B5C8E80F87AFE083BDA" bold="true" box="[396,420,2009,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">D.</emphasis>
The plants in fruiting stage.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="6483AEE13D668B5F8FCAFF34FB2239E5" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2C26FD6A3D668B5F8FCAFF34FEB53DF4" blockId="2.[151,1436,151,448]" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="1EED21783D668B5F8FCAFF34FDAC3C85" bold="true" box="[198,512,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—So far, 
<taxonomicName id="EB9986E93D668B5F8D7FFF3BFC8B3C85" authorityName="Memariani &amp; Joharchi" authorityYear="2012" box="[627,807,152,177]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aladaghense">
<emphasis id="1EED21783D668B5F8D7FFF3BFC8B3C85" box="[627,807,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">A. aladaghense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in higher elevations of Aladagh range and Salook summit in NE 
<collectingCountry id="548EBDFA3D668B5F8E92FF1DFE613CEC" box="[414,461,190,216]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="B4A2E1EF3D668B5F8ED1FF1DFD8A3CEC" box="[477,550,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1014,1035]" captionTargetBox="[332,1254,502,995]" captionTargetId="figure-481@2.[332,1254,502,995]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution map of Allium sect. Asteroprason subsect. Asteroprason including the new species, A. aladaghense (white circle) and its closely related species, A. kuhsorkhense (black circle), according to the vouchers seen by the authors." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5061130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5061130/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). It grows on north and northwest facing stony slopes, between 
<quantity id="EB61508F3D668B5F8A14FF1DFF023CCB" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.475" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.35" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" unit="m" value="2475.0" valueMax="2600.0" valueMin="2350.0">2350–2600 m</quantity>
<emphasis id="1EED21783D668B5F8FBBFF46FF5E3CCA" box="[183,242,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">a.s.l.</emphasis>
, in mountain steppes usually inhabited by thorn-cushion plants such as 
<taxonomicName id="EB9986E93D668B5F8B65FF46FCB93D12" authority="(Jaubert &amp; Spach 1842: 163) Linczevski (1952: 370)" authorityName="Linczevski" authorityPageNumber="370" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Jaubert &amp; Spach" baseAuthorityPageNumber="163" baseAuthorityYear="1842" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Acantholimon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erinaceum">
